item.title: 'Will not halt Axis of Resistance': Iran reacts to Hamas leader Sinwar's death
item.description: Iran's Supreme Leader, Ayatollah Khamenei, extends condolences on the death of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar, emphasizing that Hamas will persevere. Despite Sinwar’s death, Khamenei reassures Iran's unwavering support for the Palestinian resistance, highlighting the resilience of the resistance front against Israel.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Watch: Israeli tank striking Yahya Sinwar's Gaza shelter before conducting ground raid
item.description: The Israel Defense Forces released footage of an operation that resulted in the death of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar, who orchestrated the October 7 attacks on Israel. Sinwar was targeted in a building by tank fire. Israel confirmed his death through forensic tests. Prime Minister Netanyahu declared this a significant blow to Hamas, but stated the conflict in Gaza continues.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Chinese drone manufacturer DJI sues Pentagon over blacklisting
item.description: Drone manufacturer DJI filed a lawsuit against the US department of defense, challenging its designation as a 'Chinese military company.' DJI claims it produces consumer and commercial drones, and is not controlled by the Chinese military. The lawsuit follows Washington's increased scrutiny of Chinese tech companies over national security concerns.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Cuba blackout: Millions plunged into darkness after power plant failure
item.description: Cuba faces a nationwide blackout after the Antonio Guiteras thermoelectric plant ceased operations, triggering a total grid failure. Millions remain without power as officials scramble to restart plants. Emergency measures include school closures. The crisis exacerbates existing shortages of food, fuel, water, and medicine.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Trump sales tax': Obama warns US people of Trump's big economic plan
item.description: Former US President Barack Obama criticized Donald Trump's economic policies during a speech in Arizona, attributing early successes of Trump's economy to his own administration's groundwork. Obama described Trump's tariff strategies as harmful and claimed that financial missteps, including tax cuts, led to instability, sparking mixed reactions on social media.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'America is ready to turn the page': Obama throws weight behind Harris as election enters final stretch
item.description: Former President Obama campaigned for Kamala Harris in Tucson, criticizing Donald Trump for sowing division. Obama questioned Trump's competence and mental state, citing his bizarre public appearances. He called for unity and urged the crowd to support Kamala Harris, expressing optimism for America's future. Obama emphasized the need to turn the page on Trump's presidency.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: North American Sikh organisation calls for dialogue between India and Canada amidst rising tension
item.description: The diplomatic tensions between India and Canada over the murder of Khalistan activist Hardeep Singh Nijjar have serious implications for the Sikh community globally. Satnam Singh Chahal of NAPA highlights concerns about identity, safety, and polarisation within the diaspora. Rising incidents of discrimination and divided opinions are exacerbating challenges for Sikhs in North America.
item.dc:creator: Ishani Duttagupta

item.title: 'Get that fat pig off the couch': Trump's remark at Michigan rally sparks outrage
item.description: Republican candidate Donald Trump, during a rally in Detroit, urged women to get their 'fat' husbands off the couch to vote for him, sparking widespread criticism on social media. Trump's remarks, calling husbands 'fat pigs,' have been condemned as demeaning. Trump lags in national support among women, with early voting starting soon in Michigan.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US sanctions 2 Indians for 'ties' to Houthis transporting Iranian oil
item.description: The US has sanctioned 18 entities, including two individuals of Indian descent, for their involvement with a Houthi network transporting Iranian oil. This network funds Houthi attacks on Israel and disrupts shipping in the Red Sea. The companies involved are linked to the Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps-Quds Force.

item.title: North Korea claims it discovered the remains of a South Korean drone in its capital
item.description: North Korea claimed to discover a South Korean drone in Pyongyang, alleging it was proof of South Korean military infiltrations and propaganda activities. South Korea dismissed the claim as unilateral and unworthy of a response. Rising tensions between the nations include North Korea's threats of retaliation and ongoing psychological warfare tactics.

item.title: ‘4 more ministers of Trudeau cabinet planning departures’
item.description: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau is planning a cabinet shuffle as several ministers, including Carla Qualtrough and MarieClaude Bibeau, decide not to run in the next election. This move comes amid growing discontent over the Liberal Party’s slump in the polls and pressure to compete with Conservative leader Pierre Poilievre.

item.title: Elon Musk's SpaceX successfully launches 20 Starlink satellites
item.description: SpaceX successfully launched a Falcon 9 rocket carrying 20 Starlink satellites, including 13 with Direct to Cell capabilities, from Cape Canaveral. The first-stage booster returned to Earth, landing on the drone ship 'Just Read the Instructions'. This launch marks the 17th mission for the booster, supporting various missions including OneWeb 2 and Intelsat 40e.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US elections: Kamala Harris questions Trump's physical stamina; former President hits back
item.description: Kamala Harris expressed concerns about 78-year-old Donald Trump's physical ability to serve as president, questioning his stamina. In response, Trump denied fatigue claims and emphasized his poll strength. Harris also criticized Trump's portrayal of the January 6 Capitol attack. Both candidates are actively campaigning in Michigan, a critical battleground state, with polls showing a tight race.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Bangladesh interim government says polls possible in 2025
item.description: Bangladesh's interim government anticipates that parliamentary elections could realistically happen next year after forming a new election commission and finalizing an updated voter list. However, there are ongoing legal actions against top Awami League leaders, including Sheikh Hasina, which could impact their participation.

item.title: Watch: Trump faces mic malfunction in Detroit rally, says he won't pay for 'stupid company'
item.description: Donald Trump’s rally in Detroit was plagued by technical issues when his microphone cut out, leaving him waiting for nearly 20 minutes. Amid chants of support from the crowd, Trump eventually resumed, taking a jab at the equipment provider.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Oakland bushfire destroys homes, forces hundreds to evacuate as blaze spreads
item.description: A significant bushfire erupted in Oakland Hills near Interstate 580, consuming seven homes and covering 13 acres within hours. Authorities issued evacuation orders, directing residents to Burckhalter Elementary School. No injuries were reported as 120 firefighters and aircraft worked to control the blaze amid red flag warnings and diablo winds. The fire's cause is still unknown.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US Republicans accuse Britain of foreign interference after Labour sends 100 staff to campaign for Harris
item.description: US Republicans accuse Britain's Labour Party of foreign election interference after members went to the US to campaign for Kamala Harris. Controversy arose when a LinkedIn post revealed nearly 100 Labour staffers participating, prompting legal and political backlash. Involvement is personal, not Labour-organized.
item.dc:creator: Naomi Canton

item.title: Trump says he was 'amazed that Harvey Weinstein got scholnged'
item.description: Donald Trump, during an interview on the Dan Bongino Show, discussed how he was surprised Harvey Weinstein faced severe punishment despite being backed by Democrats. Trump referred to Weinstein as the 'king of the woke' and said Democrats typically protect their own. “But boy — you don’t know him well, I don’t know him well, but I watched that and it was amazing. So when they do get hit, they get hit. But that’s the only one I can think of, normally they protect everybody,” he continued. “What they did was Adams, I think, is very suspect.”
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Are Meghan and Harry buying a house in Portugal? King Charles has a message
item.description: Royal experts are also aware that Harry and Meghan are buying a house in Portugal and they believe that King Charles' message to them would be of indifference. King Charles is not going to "concern himself" with the news, experts claimed. King Charles evicted them from their Windsor property after they left the family and defamed the family in the public but the King will not be perturbed by the news.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Surprise battlefield encounter led to Sinwar's death, say Israelis
item.description: Israeli soldiers on a routine patrol in Gaza encountered Yahya Sinwar, the Hamas chief, and killed him alongside two militants in a firefight. Sinwar had been elusive since October 2023, but his identity was confirmed through dental records, fingerprints, and DNA testing.
